{
  "message": "test(polynomial): lock Chebyshev arithmetic degree-handling parity\n\nAdded 12 golden fixtures for chebadd/chebsub/chebmul/chebval against\nnp.polynomial.chebyshev, which each had a single fixture. Targets the\ndegree-arithmetic surface (unequal input lengths, short-long vs\nlong-short symmetry, scalar scaling, degree-N \u00d7 degree-M products).\n\n- chebadd: equal-length, short+long, long+short symmetry\n- chebsub: equal-length, short-long (sign flip), long-short tail\n- chebmul: scalar-times-vector, (T0+T1)\u00b2 identity [1.5,2,0.5],\n  quadratic\u00d7quadratic degree-4 textbook, linear\u00d7cubic degree-4\n- chebval: T2 at symmetric [-1,0,1] \u2192 [1,-1,1], single-point 0.5\n  evaluation of 1\u00b7T0+2\u00b7T1+3\u00b7T2 \u2192 0.5\n\n131 polynomial_differential cases total. Suite stays green.\n\nCo-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.7 (1M context) <noreply@anthropic.com>",
